frameDefinitions: A Cause or Agent causes a Patient to undergo a change of phase.
In this frame an Agent or Cause changes the consistency of a Patient from its Initial_state to a Result.
An Agent causes a Patient to be more strong, often resulting in something that is more secure and safe.
An Agent has done or omitted to do an Act or is responsible for the obtaining of a State_of_affairs, which a Judge deems to constitute a violation of an obligation or a moral guideline.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
frameExamples: Donna <t>thinned</t> the soup with chicken broth.
Local Serbs are <t>strengthening</t> their grip on a narrow corridor along the Sava River between two large Serbian areas.
Kim failed to fully <t>justify</t> his decision.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
